        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 16 at 10:57PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 1057 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from Silver Lake to Antioch. Movement was southeast
at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lake Catherine, Wadsworth, Lindenhurst, Lake Villa, Old Mill Creek,
Antioch, Russell, Venetian Village, Channel Lake, Grandwood Park, and
Waukegan.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
